Arguments will have R, #, x, and i in parentheses behind them. These are the types of data they can be. R is a register, # is any number/string, x is a memory register, and i is an input(1-84)

MOV destination, source
Sets register destination(R) to source(R#xi)
ADD destination, source1, source2
Sets register destination(R) to source1(R#xi) - source2(R#xi)
SUB destination, source1, source2
Sets register destination(R) to source1(R#xi)  - source2(R#xi)
CMP source1, source2
Subtracts source1(R#xi) from source2(R#xi) and sets flags
LDR destination, address
Loads memory address(x) into register destination(R)
STR source, address
Stores register source(R) at memory address address(x)
DRWCIR x, y, radius, hex, texture
Draws a circle at (x(R#xi), y(R#xi)) with a radius of radius(R#xi), colour of hex(R#xi), and texture texture(R#xi) Texture is a costume number in the GPU
DRWSQR x1, y1, x2, y2, hex
Draws a square from (x1(R#xi), y1(R#xi)) to (x2(R#xi), y2(R#xi)) with a colour of hex(R#xi)
DRWTXT text, x, y, align, size, brightness, colour
Writes text(R#xi) at (x(R#xi), y(R#xi)) with an alignment of align(R#xi), size of size(R#xi), brightness of brightness(R#xi), and colour of hex(R#xi)
DRWLNE x1, y1, x2, y2, radius, hex
Draws a line from (x1(R#xi), y1(R#xi)) to (x2(R#xi), y2(R#xi)) with a thickness of radius(R#xi) and colour of hex(R#xi)
B line
Moves the program index to line(R#xi)
BEQ flag, line
Moves the program index to line(R#xi) if flag flag is true
BNE flag line
Moves the program index to line(R#xi) if flag flag is false
MUL destination, source1, source2
Sets register destination(R) to source1(R#xi) * source2(R#xi)
DIV destination, source1, source2
Sets register destination(R) to source1(R#xi) / source2(R#xi)
CMB destination, source1, source2
Sets register destination(R) to source1(R#xi) joined to source2(R#xi)
SIN destination, source
Sets register destination(R) to sine of source(R#xi)
COS destination, source
Sets register destination(R) to cosine of source(R#xi)
